Karun Nair smashed his first ever century as India reached 463 for five at lunch on the fourth day of the fifth and final Test against England in Chennai on Monday.The right-handed batsman was at the crease on 122 alongside Ravichandran Ashwin on nine after the hosts resumed the day on 391-4. India trail England&#8217;s 477 by 14 runs with five wickets remaining in the first innings.-AFP